content:
Salesforce generates a unique Embedded Service code snippet from information you provide during setup. Copy and paste the code snippet to include chat on your web pages. Add the optional meta tag code snippet to improve performance for both mobile and desktop.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Embedded Service setup is available in Lightning Experience, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud.
To set up Embedded Chat: Customize Application AND Modify Metadata.

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. Migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date to avoid service interruptions.

Here are the steps to add your code snippet:

From Setup, enter Embedded Service in the Quick Find box.
Select the Embedded Service deployment by clicking the arrow beside the deployment name and selecting View.
In the Embedded Service configuration page, go to the Embedded Service code snippets section and click Get Code.
Copy the chat code snippet and paste it above the closing </body> tag on your web page.
Paste the meta code snippet into every web page where you want the chat window to appear.

If there are issues with behavior on other devices, update your <meta> tag to the code snippet thatâ€™s provided.
title: Adding Embedded Service to a Website
